`,c.jsx(r.p,{children:"Before building a Redis server that stores a key, expires a value, or replicates a write, we need to choose a language it should understand from the client. The understanding begins at the wire protocol."}),`
`,c.jsxs(r.p,{children:["Since we wanted this to be Redis compatible, we will choose the same protocol that Redis uses to communicate, called RESP: Redis Serialization Protocol. It is a complete specification for how bytes transfer between a client and server. Every command that you call, ",c.jsx(r.code,{children:"GET"}),", ",c.jsx(r.code,{children:"SET"}),", ",c.jsx(r.code,{children:"EXPIRE"}),", passes through RESP on its way in and out."]}),`
